The median age of reported malaria cases was 33 (range: 1–84 years) and 1,892 (69%) cases occurred in persons aged 20–50 years (Figure 3
). Migrant laborers, farmers, businessmen, and urban workers constituted 72% (1,965/2,738) of malaria cases (Figure 4
). Moreover, the proportion of businessmen increased and the proportion of migrant laborers decreased in recent years.
